entries.femaleVariant: My husband died in that tower.
Hey, gramps. I know you.
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="外せ" t="Leave us." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="直接話をする" t="I wish to look him in the eye." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="人は嘘をつき、自分自身を欺く" t="I have found that people lie, most often deceiving themselves." b="" a=""/>
Give your buddy a chance to speak?
Let us try once more.
Gonna give good cop over there a chance to say something? C'mooon…
How did you acquire fissile material?
I know that old man.
Which terrorist organization do you belong to?
Your associates – who are they?
How did you acquire fissile material?
Your boss looks unimpressed.
Boss don't look too pleased with your efforts.
But there are fates worse than death…
I didn't want him to die.
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="だが死者は違う" t="Not so the dead..." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="死者は雄弁だが、彼らは決して嘘をつかない" t="The dead are so very, very loud. And yet, lying is not in their nature." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="死者の言葉には… 慎ましさがある" t="It is so... humbling –  to listen to the dead speak." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="始めろ" t="Begin." b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="なぜ… このようなことを？" t="Why did you do this?" b="" a=""/>
Why did you do this?
To bring an end to the madness you wreak.
Hot damn – done and gone.
Aargh…
